  // ===== EVENTS =====
  // Evelyn gives farmer key to solarium
  "Events.EvelynKey.1": "Hello, dear.#$b#I'm so impressed with you and all of the work you've done since you came here. The flowers you've been growing are just beautiful.$1",
  "Events.EvelynKey.2": "So I wanted to give you this. It's the key to the solarium above the spa. I found it gathering dust in my kitchen drawer.$0",
  "Events.EvelynKey.GotKey": "You got the solarium key!",
  "Events.EvelynKey.3": "I can't make the hike into the mountains anymore to look after the old solarium like I used to... not with my knees the way they are.$2#$b#I used to tend a little garden up there where I grew seedlings for the flowerbeds in town. It's been sitting locked up and empty for ages now.$2",
  "Events.EvelynKey.4": "It is a relief to know the solarium will be in good hands again.#$b#You take good care of it for me, @, and I hope it brings you joy.$1",
  "Events.EvelynKey.SolariumAccess": "You are now able to access the solarium above the spa.",

  // Robin first visit to solarium (after player enters first time)
  "Events.RobinSolarium.1Ladder": "Oh, hey @! I didn't know anyone would be here!#$b#I heard Evelyn was handing the key over to you, so I wanted to swing by and make sure the ladder was safe.",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.1Lift": "Oh, hey @! I didn't know anyone would be here!#$b#I heard Evelyn was handing the key over to you, so I wanted to swing by and make sure the lift was safe.",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.2Ladder": "Oh yes, the ladder's solid, but the hinge on the hatch was sticking.#$b#Nothing a bit of elbow grease couldn't fix.$1",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.2Lift": "Oh yes, the lift's solid, but the hinge on the door was sticking.#$b#Nothing a bit of elbow grease couldn't fix.$1",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.3": "This place is even bigger on the inside!",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.4": "With the way they reinforced the floor, and how high the ceiling is, this place has a lot of potential.#$b#I know Evelyn was excited about flowers, but have you considered growing fruit trees in the solarium too?#$b#You have the space for them to thrive up here year-round.",
  "Events.RobinSolarium.5": "Well if you do plant fruit trees, feel free to bring me any extra peaches you harvest!$1#$b#Oh, I'll oil up that old hinge for you before I head back.",

  // Caroline and Pierre visit player (4 and 6 are Pierre lines)
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.1": "Hello, @! Evelyn mentioned she'd handed the solarium over to you. That was really sweet of her... she does think of you as family.",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.2": "Since you opened it up again, Pierre and I went to take a look around.#$b#The light in the solarium is just lovely... it's the sort of place any plant would thrive.#$b#Hmm... maybe I could bring a few plants up from my sunroom so they can enjoy the view.$1",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.3": "Oh! Pierre suggested we... well...$2",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.4": "We left a copy of the shop's newest magazine for you. You'll need a lot of seeds and saplings to fill that place up!$1",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.5": "It's sitting on the table where you can't miss it.$2#$b#We just wanted to swing by on our way back to town, but we'd better get going. Take care, @.",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.6": "Hope to see you soon!",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.2.Piper": "Since you opened it up again, Piper and I went to take a look around.#$b#The light in the solarium is just lovely... it's the sort of place any plant would thrive.#$b#Hmm... maybe I could bring a few plants up from my sunroom so they can enjoy the view.$1",
  "Events.CarolineMagazine.3.Piper": "Oh! Piper suggested we... well...$2",

  // Linus's new shelter
  "Events.LinusNewShelter.1": "Hello, @.#$b#I noticed you and a few others coming up here. I was curious, so I decided to come have a look for myself.#$b#It's a great place to get out of the cold, isn't it?#$b#A little warmth does the spirit good.$1",

  // ===== DIALOGUE (TOPIC) =====
